MESSAGE.value:
Create login example
It combines the event bus messaging with JSON serialization.

Move Launcher module to Vert.x
The project now uses Maven, and each module is a different verticle.

Implement event listener
Gotta clean the generics

Improve handle method
It now assures that the event can be handled or fails.

Create run configuration
Just `./gradlew run` and it will start the launcher with redeploy.

Simplify handlers
Only one handler per event.

Move CMS module to vertx
And with this, we're done. It's bretty cool.

Change request handler, fix config
The request handlers now accept a RoutingContext instead of an HttpServerRequest. Fixed the verticles not having the same configuration instance.

Handlers can end the request
If a request handler returns null, it will assume the handler properly called the `HttpServerResponse.end` method.

Create register handler
Gotta make the MessageCodec to send POJO through the event bus.

Reworked event system
Handlers are registered in their own consumers and the event is a JsonObject with the data.

Create String utils
The class StringUtils contains util methods for strings. Also created `Handler.fail(message)` to return an error result.
